
[1]compensation

   COMPENSATION, n.

   1. That which is given or received as an equivalent for services, debt,
   want, loss, or suffering; amends; remuneration; recompense.

   All other debts may compensation find.

   The pleasures of life are no compensation for the loss of divine favor
   and protection.

   2. In law, a set-off; the payment of a debt by a credit of equal
   amount.
